## Context
The divergence pipeline produces tables and figures but they are not
yet wired into any document. The technical report needs updated
structural breaks section. The old compute_breakpoints.py results
coexist without conflict but create confusion.

## Actions

### Wire into technical report
1. Complete ticket 0034: `content/_includes/structural-breaks-v2.md`.
2. Update `content/technical-report.qmd` to include the new section.
3. Reference the convergence figure and the per-method divergence figures.

### Deprecate old breakpoints
4. Add deprecation comment to `compute_breakpoints.py` header:
   "Superseded by compute_divergence.py. Retained for comparison."
5. Remove old breakpoint Makefile targets from the main Makefile
   (or gate them behind a `legacy-breakpoints` target).
6. Do NOT delete the old script — it serves as comparison baseline.

### Add make check-divergence
7. Add target to divergence.mk:
   ```make
   .PHONY: check-divergence
   check-divergence:
       python3 -m pytest tests/test_divergence.py tests/test_changepoints.py \
           tests/test_embedding_sensitivity.py -v
   ```

### Parallel execution documentation
8. Document in divergence.mk header comment:
   `make -j15 divergence-tables` runs all 15 methods in parallel.
   Tested: no race conditions (each script writes a distinct file).

## Test
`make technical-report` builds without error and includes the new
structural breaks section.

## Exit criteria
New results visible in rendered technical report. Old results clearly
marked as legacy. `make check-divergence` works. Parallel docs added.
